Detailed Description

cvmx_mio_emm_dma_fifo_cmd

This register specifies a command that is loaded into the eMMC internal DMA FIFO. The FIFO is used to queue up operations for the MIO_EMM_DMA_CFG/MIO_EMM_DMA_ADR when the DMA completes successfully. Writes to this register store both the MIO_EMM_DMA_FIFO_CMD and the MIO_EMM_DMA_FIFO_ADR contents into the FIFO and increment the MIO_EMM_DMA_FIFO_CFG[COUNT] field.

Note: This register has a similar format to the MIO_EMM_DMA_CFG register with the exception that the EN and CLR fields are absent. These are supported in the MIO_EMM_DMA_FIFO_CFG.
